The pseudocode of a function fun () is given below:
fun(int A[0,…,n-1]){
  for i=0 to n-2
    for j=0 to n-i-2
      if (A[j]>A[j+1])
        then swap A[j] and A[j+1]
}
Let A[0, ...,29] be an array storing 30 distinct integers in descending order. The number of swap operations that will be performed, if the function fun () is called with A[0, ...,29] as argument, is ____. (Answer in integer)

